tafsir[5]{c,v,t}:
  51,31,"Abraham (peace be upon him) said to the angels: “What is you case? And what do you intend?”"
  51,32,"The angels said in reply: “Allah has sent us to a criminal people who commit despicable sins."
  51,33,"So that I can send upon them stones of hard clay."
  51,45,"So they were unable to repel the punishment that befell them nor did they have any power to defend themselves with."
  51,51,"And do not make alongside Allah another deity to worship besides Him. I am a clear warner to you."